Wim Pretorius, News24(ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Vereeniging &ndash; Two men were found dead on the banks of the Vaal River in Vereeniging on Saturday. The South African Police Search and Rescue team found the men after they were reported missing earlier in the week. According to ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring, the men, who appear to be in their 20s, are suspected to have drowned. "It was apparent that the men had been dead for some time," Meiring said in a statement. Police are investigating and no further information is available at the moment.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.